               <region notBefore="1991" type="RegionalState" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5932Tegray">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy</region>
               
               <settlement type="warada" when="2010-12-04" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3293GantaA">Gāntā ʾAfašum</settlement>
               <settlement type="tabiya" when="2010-12-04" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7220Gullat">Gullāt</settlement>
               <settlement type="qushat" when="2010-12-04" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7221Makoda">Maḵodʿa</settlement>
            

               <location>
                  <geo>14.189278 39.362222</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2370.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1600" notAfter="1600">1600-1600</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Possibly diring the time of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6229LebnaDe">King Lǝbnā Dǝngǝl</persName> (r. <date>1508-1540</date>), re-established late 17th or early 18th cent. 
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6951Mazgaba">Mazgaba Śǝllāse</persName>, the late 17th - early 18th-cent. head of Gunda Gunde, played a role in the establishement of the local monastic community.</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gadam. Some 10 monks were residing in the monastery at the time of the visit. 
                     </ab>
                  <ab type="description">
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Sites/GKM.tif">
                           <desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</desc>
                        </graphic>
                     </figure>
                     22 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm001">GKM-001</ref> "The Spiritual Elder"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm002">GKM-002</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm003">GKM-003</ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm004">GKM-004</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm005">GKM-005</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm006">GKM-006</ref> "The Rite of the Holy Week"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm007">GKM-007</ref> "Homily of the Living One"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm008">GKM-008</ref> "Pauline Epistles"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm009">GKM-009</ref> "Synaxarion (September)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm010">GKM-010</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm011">GKM-011</ref> "Synaxarion (March)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm012">GKM-012</ref> "Miracles of Mikaʾel"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm013">GKM-013</ref> "Vita of Mäzgäbä Śǝllase"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm014">GKM-014</ref> "Psalter"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm015">GKM-015</ref> "Prayer of Incense"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm016">GKM-016</ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm017">GKM-017</ref> "The Covenant of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm018">GKM-018</ref> "Psalter"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm019">GKM-019</ref> "Collection of Maryam Texts and hymns"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm020">GKM-020</ref> "Prayers of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm021">GKM-021</ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite; The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgkm022">GKM-022</ref> fragments of a Missal and a Psalter.</ab>
                  <ab type="tabot"> 
                     <measure quantity="44"/>   Tābots: said to be "44", i.e. very many, both wooden and marble; specifically were mentioned tābots of 
                     <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10775Trinity">Trinity</persName>, <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6951Mazgaba">Mazgaba Śǝllāse</persName>, 
                     <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName>, <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh#n3MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName>, <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</persName>.  
                     Possibly there exists also specifically <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CovenantMercy">Kidāna Mǝḥrat</ref>.
</ab>               
               </note>
